header
  .container
    h1= current_page.data.title
    #introduction Do you know your websites could become awfully slow or don't even load in China? GFWaaS helps you test the performance and identify the underlying bottlenecks.
    = partial 'form'
    .credit Photo by <a href="https://www.flickr.com/photos/jcb2u/1174985565/">jcb2u</a>. Modified under <a href="https://creativecommons.org/licenses/by-nd/2.0/">CC BY-ND 2.0</a>.
.container
  #sections
    section.why
      .row.justify-content-center
        .col-md-10.col-lg-10
          h2
            span.subtitle Why & What does it mean?
            span.title China's national Internet firewall, a.k.a The Great Firewall (GFW), together with countless political and technological restrictions, often makes websites outside of China awfully slow to load or even inaccessible. <br />For example, websites built on the following services could be blocked or barely usable in China.
          - services.each do |s|
            <i class="#{s[:icon]}" title="#{s[:name]}" style="color: #{s[:color]}"></i>
    section.what
      .row.justify-content-center
        .col-md-10.col-lg-10
          h2
            span.subtitle Okay. What to do?
            span.title Generally, you either figure out a way to host your website in China (a lot of paperwork) or optimize your website for China. Whichever way you choose, you always need to test your website for optimal user experience in China. That's where GFWaaS can help.
      .row
        - features.each do |f|
          .col-md.feature class="#{'last-child' if f == features.last}"
            h3 <i class="#{f[:icon]}"></i> #{f[:title]}
